af37; margin-bottom: 15px; font-family: \"Cinzel\", serif;'>Ihya 'Ulum al-Din Commentary</h4><div class='ihya-entry'><div style='margin-bottom: 10px;'><a href='../books/vol4_Vol4-book6.doc.txt' target='_blank' class='badge badge-light' style='color: #666; border: 1px solid #ddd; cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none;'>ğŸ“– Vol 4: Love, Longing, and Intimacy</a></div><div class='ihya-text' style='font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; margin-bottom: 10px;'>Indeed, he whose aim is the Lord of the Abode [rabb al-dar] and the Possessor of Sovereignty [malik al-mulk], and who is overcome by nothing but His love through sincerity [ikhlas] and truthfulness [sidq], He will cause to dwell \"in a seat of truth [fi maq'ad sidq], near a Sovereign Omnipotent [mulk muqtadir].\" Thus, the righteous [al-abrar] will roam in gardens and delight in paradises with wide-eyed maidens and immortal youths. But those brought near [al-muqarrabun] are constant in the Presence [al-hadra], their gaze fixed upon It, and they deem the bliss of the gardens insignificant compared to an atom of It. For some people are preoccupied with satisfying the appetite of the belly and the private parts, while others are for intimate companionship [mujalasa]. And for this reason, the Messenger of God, peace and blessings be upon him, said: \"The majority of the inhabitants of Paradise are the simple-minded, and 'Illiyyun is for those of intellect.\" And when understandings fell short of grasping the meaning of 'Illiyyun, He magnified its matter, saying: \"And what will make you know what 'Illiyyun is?\" just as the Almighty has said: \"The Striking Calamity! What is the Striking Calamity? And what will make you know what the Striking Calamity is?\"</div><div class='ihya-arabic' style='font-size: 1.2em; line-height: 1.8; color: #555; text-align: right; direction: rtl; font-family: \"Traditional Arabic\", serif; background: #fff; padding: 10px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid #eee;'>ÙˆÙ…Ù† ÙƒØ§Ù